article.headline: Norfolk St. 66, Bethune-Cookman 52
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Corey Lyons scored 20 points and Calvin Brown and Tony Murphy each added 13 to lead Norfolk State to a 66-52 win over Bethune-Cookman on Monday night. The Spartans (8-13, 8-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) outshot Bethune-Cookman, making 52.4 percent to the Wildcats' 38.5 percent. Lyons also added six rebounds for the Spartans. Jimmy Hudson led the Wildcats with 16 points, while John Anderson added 13 points and 8 rebounds. The Wildcats (4-17, 2-9) outrebounded Norfolk State 31-28.
